This paper is about randomized methods for neural networks, specifically stochastic configuration algorithms for SC networks. The paper discusses data modeling techniques for regression and classification problems, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
